            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-11-05 20:07:19" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to being white or very light in color; applies to (parts of) the human body, animals, plants, inanimate objects</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>white</Gloss>
                <Gloss>light color</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The term λευκός also occurs in {S:04300403500048} in speaking of fields being ‘white for the harvest,’ but in a number of languages it would be quite impossible to use the same term for the ripe condition of a harvest as in the case of the color of wool or snow. Furthermore, there may be a serious difficulty in speaking of wool as being ‘white,’ since in many parts of the world, wool is not regarded as being particularly white.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
